info.senderName: NWS Sioux Falls (Southeastern SD, Southwestern MN, and Northwestern IA)
info.headline: Wind Advisory issued November 15 at 9:46PM CST until November 16 at 7:00PM CST by NWS Sioux Falls
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM TO 7 PM CST THURSDAY... * WHAT...Southwest to west winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 45 to 50 mph expected. * WHERE...In Iowa, Osceola, Dickinson and Clay Counties. In Minnesota, Lincoln, Lyon, Murray, Cottonwood, Nobles and Jackson Counties. * WHEN...From 9 AM to 7 PM CST Thursday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. The strong winds could result in rapid fire spread through very dry grasses.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects. Use caution to avoid sparking a grass fire.
